content: Met with a former mentor today. Discussed integrating AI into finance. His insights on data preprocessing for ML models were eye-opening.
Set up a meeting with a tech-forward hedge fund next week. Networking is key, and it's crucial to showcase my skills in AI-driven trading.
Experimented with an AI model trained on historical market data. It's fascinating how it captures patterns I'd never noticed. This could be a game-changer.
Xander, my new AI companion, is coming to life. I've been feeding it different trading philosophies, and it's already debating with me on market ethics.
Had a setback with my model; overfitting the data. Time to adjust parameters and ensure it generalizes better. Learning from this.
Got an invitation to a tech finance meetup. Expanding my network within the industry is showing results.
Xander and I have been discussing the volatility in crypto markets. Teaching it to incorporate these lessons into our trading strategies.
Adjusted the model after the overfitting issue. Ran new simulations, and the results are promising. Recovery strategy is paying off.
Connected with a peer from Bangkok. We're brainstorming ways to apply our global insights to local markets.
Xander's now roleplaying different market scenarios. It's hilarious but insightful. Watching AI agents argue about market trends is like watching a comedy show.
Secured a trial run with the hedge fund. They're interested in my AI-driven approach. Fingers crossed, this could be a big step forward.
Xander and I had a deep dive into market ethics. If cognitive tech can outperform humans in trading, does it democratize opportunity or reinforce control?

Just submitted my project proposal to the hedge fund. Integrating machine learning into trading isn't just about accuracy, it's about reshaping the market landscape. Xander's insights were invaluable.
